    "name": "Moldwretch",
    "type": "monster",
    "sections": [
        {
            "name": "Description",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "While they are usually reclusive and aren\u2019t actively malevolent, moldwretches often come into conflict with adventurers who clear away patches of mold during dungeon exploration. They get along well with vegepygmies, but loathe and fear fungus queens (see page 130). A moldwretch is only 3 feet tall but is very dense and weighs 120 pounds."
        }
    ],
