        "special_abilities": [
            {
                "type": "stat_block_section",
                "subtype": "special_ability",
                "name": "Mold Symbiosis",
                "ability_type": "Extraordinary",
                "ability_type_abbrev": "Ex",
                "text": "A moldwretch forms bonds with mold hazards by spending time within their areas of effect. A moldwretch can bond with only one mold at a time, and the symbiotic bond forms only after the moldwretch spends 8 hours in contact with the hazard. A moldwretch is immune to fungal hazards. Three example mold symbiosis effects are detailed below. <br/><br/><i>Brown Mold:</i> The moldwretch is immune to fire, and fire-based attacks restore a number of hit points to it equal to half the damage the attacks would normally deal. Its spores deal 2d6 points of cold damage. <br/><br/><i>Russet Mold:</i> The moldwretch\u2019s spores expose targets to the effects of russet mold (<i>Pathfinder RPG Bestiary</i> 273). <br/><br/><i>Yellow Mold:</i> The moldwretch\u2019s spores expose targets to the effects of yellow mold (<i>Pathfinder RPG Core Rulebook</i> 416). "
            },
            {
                "type": "stat_block_section",
                "subtype": "special_ability",
                "name": "Spores",
                "ability_type": "Extraordinary",
                "ability_type_abbrev": "Ex",
                "text": "A moldwretch\u2019s tentacle and spore launch attacks expose their targets to the creature\u2019s spores, which have an effect linked to the moldwretch\u2019s mold symbiosis. A successful DC 19 Fortitude save negates the additional effect of a moldwretch\u2019s spores. The save DC is Constitution-based."
            }
        ]
